MBOMBELA &#8211; Minister for state security, Mr David Mahlobo, has strongly denied that he had played any role in the termination of the Pathfinder Corporation&#8217;s contract with SANParks in June 2014.A contract between SANParks and the Pathfinder Corporation, a company employed by the Kruger National Park (KNP) to render strategic, specialised risk-management services pertaining to anti-poaching for SANParks, was terminated on June 3 of that year.This revelation was made in the documentary The Poachers&#8217; Pipeline which aired on Al Jazeera on Sunday.